<TITLE> 14 die in road crashes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  At least 14 people were killed in road accidents across the country on Sunday. In Mymensingh, 9 people died and 20 others were injured as a bus crashed into a roadside ditch on the Dhaka-Mymensingh highway at Bhaluka early Sunday. Additional police super SM Akhteruzzaman said the Mymensingh-bound bus lost control as it veered at high speed to avoid a truck at Meherabari at around 1am. Three people died on the spot, he said. Ten critically injured passengers were admitted to Bhaluka Upazila Health Complex, where four succumbed to injuries. The remaining six were later shifted to Mymensingh Medical College Hospital, where another two died, Akhteruzzaman said. In Comilla, Three including a mother and her son were killed and 10 injured as a Dhaka-bound bus skidded off the road and fell into a ditch at Purnomati area under Burichong upazila, police said. The injured were admitted to the upazila health complex, Md Anisur Rahman Khan, officer-in-charge of Burichong Police Station, told reporters. In Norshingdi, two passengers on a motorcycle were killed on the spot after they were knocked down by a speeding covered van near Bhatpara area, officer-in-charge of Sadar Police Station Shamim Ahmed told bdnews24.com. The victims have been identified as 'Shamim', 22, and 'Hira', 30 of Bhagdi village under Bhatpara. bdnews24.com/co
